<big><big><big><big><center><span style="font-family:Jost;">'''LEVEL 490'''</span></center></big></big></big></big>


<div class="onlydark"><div style="font-size: 96px; text-align: center; background: #002FA766; border-top: 2px solid white; border-bottom: 2px solid white; padding: 5px; border-radius: 0px; text-shadow: 0px 0px 4px #99FFFF; letter-spacing: 0.25rem; font-family:Trajan Pro;">"The Summit"</div></div>
<div class="onlylight"><div style="font-size: 96px; text-align: center; background: #00BFFF60; border-top: 2px solid white; border-bottom: 2px solid white; padding: 5px; border-radius: 0px; text-shadow: 0px 0px 4px #003262; letter-spacing: 0.25rem; font-family:Trajan Pro;">"The Summit"</div></div>


<div style="background: #d6fffa; padding: 15px; border-radius: 45px; box-shadow: 0px 0px 20px #AFAFAF inset, 0px 0px 50px #242124 inset, 0 0 75px #242124 inset; text-align:center; margin:2.5em 18em">
<span style="font-family:Trajan Pro; font-size:36px; text-shadow: 0px 0px 1.2px #808080; color:#555555;"> He who stands before this monument shall cleanse himself of the vile sin he has committed, for he shall scale the great summit ahead to cleanse himself of his scourge. </span>
</div>


<center>
That was what I saw. A stone tablet emblazoned with these words, as I stand before a mountain boasting gargantuan heights. I don't remember how I ended up here, I just know that I was being a bitch to that Megacolony back in [[Level 399]] and was blasted by cold water at full power. It's a faint memory, but it feels so vivid.

What crimes have I even done? I've only disturbed the peace, was a bit passive-aggressive towards some people, and other minor and petty crimes. It is not like I've harmed people, or have truly committed anything heinous. I slowly regain my memories, and I slowly remember the events that had unfolded, and the more I realize how small those crimes were, and how ridiculous of a punishment this is. It's almost unbelievable that I was punished like this, I still could not fathom such a fate.

'''Why?'''

The Backrooms never fail to torture its inhabitants like this. Not even the safe havens can be trusted. Such a reality is just infuriating.

But, there's only one way out of this mess. Crying it out won't help. This is my fate, and I should scale the grand summit, instead of staying here and whining about everything.

After trudging on through thick, slippery snow for fifteen minutes, I come across a rudimentary and tattered wooden shed at the base of the mountain. All it contains within are a pair of crampons, an ice axe, and an ice pick. No rope, harness, or other safety tools, just these basic equipment. These would hopefully suffice, ''hopefully''.

But before I started climbing, I thought that there might be other ways out. Noclipping is everywhere in the Backrooms, who's to say that it would be absent in this level? I naively hoped for a cheap way out, like noclipping through the snow or through some rocks. It could send me to the hellscape of [[One State]], the paradise of [[Silent Horizon]], or anything in between. While I am rusty at it, I tried meditative noclipping, yet even that had not worked after several attempts. There truly was no way out, except for up.


<div class="ua-animation ua-shrink grow-hover" style="animation-iteration-count: 0; animation-direction: reverse; animation-duration: 1.8s; animation-timing-function: ease-in; --size-quantity: 1.02; --size-duration:0.4s;">[[File:Kertz.png|center|link=|600x600px]]</div>


The initial ascensions were easy. It almost felt a bit too lenient, but this is just the very beginning. I can only guesstimate how much work I need to put for this to happen. After twenty minutes of climbing, I reached a rugged platform where I rested for a while, and then I went back to climbing. After this it felt a bit more difficult, and I notice the slope becoming gradually becoming steeper. Fortunately it was not draining my energy, so I continually climbed for about an hour until I reached another, larger and flatter platform to rest on for a bit.

Standing at the edge of the platform, I witnessed the grandeur of the mountain, and after the hour of nonstop climbing I had just endured, just staring at such a behemoth already makes me want to pass out. Not only am I nowhere near finished in my adventure, but it's only going to get harder, as I will battle steeper slopes and ferocious winds. I couldn't even pray to God, as I was in the Backrooms, where for now at least, there is no God to rescue me from... all this. I look back at the good times, from just chilling in [[Level 330]] to hanging out with other wanderers, but it's saddening now that I have to do this now.

I eventually built the courage to continue. I had no other way, but to realize, that this is destiny. I went back into climbing, with determination and dedication. It was tougher, but doable. It was harsher, but not unbearable. I could feel specks of metal chipping away at my crampons and picks, and was almost about to give up, yet I reminded myself that either I fall down to oblivion, or continue climbing no matter the cost. Every step, every swing, every breath, felt glorious.

Another hour has passed. My picks and crampons are still holding strong, and so is my courage and spirit. The peak of the mountain still seems far away from sight to me, yet I still get filled with energy with every step and swing of the way, something that feels odd to me. I know that I will find some place to take a short break somewhere, like another platform.

Eventually, after thirty more minutes, I found another platform. I've been climbing for around three hours now, and after taking a gander at the height of that behemoth, it was very clear that I was only getting started, yet I already have trouble breathing, the winds are unrelenting, the slopes getting steeper, and my tools getting weaker. I was thinking that the Backrooms were unforgiving for having someone like me do all this for a few petty crimes, and I thought, "Imagine if there exist different versions of this level, where the worse the crime, the taller the mountain and the harsher the punishment?" Kinda like [[Level 995]]. Although it is likely false, such a thought relieved me, even if it is naive.

Other questions started popping into my head. "Is all this related to Level 995's karma system? If so, what karma do I have?" "Could I meet other wanderers within this level?" "What happens if I do fall to my untimely demise?" So many questions, so little answers. But that's not the greatest of concerns, the road ahead is. As this was a fairly large platform, I looked around and see if I could find better climbing gear, and to my surprise, I did, alongside a dead body, and it answered my question. This guy fell, and was judged by the Backrooms. But, where are they now if they died? Are they in some sort of hell? I could easily just move on and enjoy my new gear, but I could not stop thinking about that dead body. I mean, I stole from a literal grave, and it scares me that this exact thing could happen to me.

But I cannot just stay here and needlessly worry. I have to climb up this mountain. It must be done, to compensate for my wrongdoings.


<div class="ua-animation ua-shrink grow-hover" style="animation-iteration-count: 0; animation-direction: reverse; animation-duration: 1.8s; animation-timing-function: ease-in; --size-quantity: 1.02; --size-duration:0.4s;">[[File:Smallworldindecision.jpg|center|link=|600x600px]]</div>


I was beginning to develop a muscle memory. I was beginning to become more efficient, and while it gets harder, I adapt quickly. I've put myself on autopilot while climbing from here on out. I was even zoning out on the edge of a cliff, that's how locked in I was.

But then, disaster struck.

About 45 minutes in, my right crampon broke, and I abruptly fell. Fortunately I was on a thick, snowy slope, so I didn't immediately fall on something and end up like that guy; my reaction time was fast enough to grab the heavy ice axe from my back and I used the back of the axe to slow down the inevitable fall. I stopped near the edge of a cliff, gripping the shaft of the axe as hard as I can for dear life. I could hear cracking coming from the rocks my axe was tethered to, so I had to think quick. I grabbed my right pick and anchored to the edge of the cliff, but I realized that there was no way for me to get my body onto the platform.

I hung there, knowing that there is no more for me. My life started to flash before me. Every happy moment that constitutes my life, from the calmness of [[Level 330]], the glory from defeating my first entity, relieving myself of that [[Entity 8|wild]] bastard, my adventures with my close buddies, all the jokes, all the fun moments, everything. I've done so much, but this is where it ends. So many things here could have killed me by now, from those close entity encounters to almost falling to [[The Void]], but being a minor nuisance to the inhabitants of [[Level 399]] was the end of the line for me. Before I finished reliving every one of my memories, my tools finally snapped, and I...


...was free-falling.

<br><br><br><br><br><br><br><br><br><br><br><br><br><br><br><br><br>
[[File:RunForYourLife_Icon.png|link=]]
{{Underline|002FA7}}
I saw myself embedded within knee-high snow. I looked around, and assumed myself to be in some form of afterlife. I slowly started to regain my consciousness and took note of my surroundings. I was on a pile of snow, one of the flat mountain platforms. I endured two minutes of excruciating pain, and then miraculously stood up. As I was adjusting my vision, I could eyeball the silhouette of a person in the distance. Hopefully they have some spare climbing tools, and maybe we can share our experiences. If not, well I've got nothing to lose at this point. 

When I walked up to the person, he seemed to be speaking in English, and I felt relieved that I could strike a conversation to them. He then noticed me and was startled for a bit, but he started approaching me after he saw I was just a regular guy. We conversed about many things, from our experiences, why we were sent here, and how we felt about this. But there was something off about this guy. The tone of his voice felt off, and he was passive aggressive towards me. Which makes sense, he's probably here for a reason. But I digress, the more we talked, the more unfriendly he became and the more angrier he sounded.

The conversation lasted around 12 minutes. At the last few minutes, this guy's insufferableness made me want to slowly back away. He could see the facial expressions I was making that suggests it, and while I was trying to be chill, he just brushed me off and pulled out a grappling gun. A GRAPPLING GUN. I was climbing this tall mountain with the most rudimentary tools, not even safety equipment, and this guy gets a whole ass grappling gun. Talk about balance. He just grappled to a ledge that was so high up it was being concealed by the fog, and he left and ghosted me on a question I had for him.

Everything in the last twenty minutes felt like a dang rollercoaster. I fell from great heights, survived, struck a conversation with this weird dude, who then ghosted me with his grappling gun, while I am left here with only one crampon and one pick. It isn't even sad, it just downright makes my blood boil. I haven't been this frustrated in months, especially in a place like the Backrooms. How did that guy even get access to such a powerful tool? I mean, karma is going to strike him back, but all that matters now is me, as with the little things I have now, how am I going to finish all this? With insufficient climbing tools, not even the strongest men would scale such a beast.

There's nothing else left on this platform, except for me and my lacking equipment. I truly have nothing to lose anymore... Have I been judged by the Backrooms?

Is this... how it all ends?

It's a fate... that I'll willingly accept.
</center>
